38 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
39 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
40 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
41 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
42 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
43 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
44  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
45 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
46 #else
47 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
48 #endif
49 #endif
50 
51 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
52 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
53 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
54 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
55 #else
56 #error "unknown compiler"
57 #endif
58 
59 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
60 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
61 #else
62 #include <cstdio>
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
64  do { \
65  fputs(msg, stderr); \
66  DNNL_TRAP(); \
67  } while (0)
68 #endif

84 struct error : public std::exception {
85  dnnl_status_t status;
86  const char *message;
87 
92  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
93  : status(status), message(message) {}
94 
96  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
97 
103  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
104  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
105  }
106 };
107 
109 template <typename T>
110 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
111  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
112  const int size = (int)v.size();
113  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
114  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
115 }
117 
119 template <typename T>
120 struct handle_traits {};
121 
135 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
136 struct handle {
137 private:
138  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
139  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
140 
141 protected:
142  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
143  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
144 
145 public:
153  handle() = default;
154 
156  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
158  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
160  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
162  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
163 
169  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
170 
176  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
177  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
178  }
179 
185  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
186  T result = data_.get();
187  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
188  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
189  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
190  return result;
191  }
192 
197  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
198 
202  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
203 
210  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
211  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
212  }
213 
220  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
221 };

375 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
376  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
377  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
378  // returns a C type.
379  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
380  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
381  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
382  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
383  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
384 }

670 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
671  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
672  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
673  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
674  } \
675 \
676  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
677  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
678  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
679  } \
680 \
681  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
682  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
683  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
684  } \
685 \
686  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
687  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
688  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
689  return lhs; \
690  } \
691 \
692  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
693  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
694  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
695  return lhs; \
696  } \
697 \
698  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
699  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
700  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
701  return lhs; \
702  } \
703 \
704  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
705  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
706  }
707 
708 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
709 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

869 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
870  friend struct primitive;
871  friend struct reorder;
872 
874  enum class kind {
876  any = dnnl_any_engine,
878  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
880  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
881  };
882 
883  using handle::handle;
884 
887  engine() = default;
888 
893  static size_t get_count(kind akind) {
894  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(akind));
895  }
896 
902  engine(kind akind, size_t index) {
903  dnnl_engine_t engine;
904  error::wrap_c_api(
905  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(akind), index),
906  "could not create an engine");
907  reset(engine);
908  }
909 
914  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
915  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
916  error::wrap_c_api(
917  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
918  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
919  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
920  reset(c_engine, true);
921  }
922 
925  kind get_kind() const {
926  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
927  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
928  "could not get kind of an engine");
929  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
930  }
931 
937  template <typename primitive_desc>
938  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
939  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
940  }
941 
942 private:
943  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
944  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
945  }
946 
947  template <typename primitive_desc>
948  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
949  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
950  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
951  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
952  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
953  return engine(c_engine, true);
954  }
955 };

985 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
986  using handle::handle;
987 
989  enum class flags : unsigned {
991  in_order = dnnl_stream_in_order,
993  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
995  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
996  };
997 
1000  stream() = default;
1001 
1007  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags) {
1008  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1009  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, aengine.get(),
1010  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags)),
1011  "could not create a stream");
1012  reset(stream);
1013  }
1014 
1016  engine get_engine() const {
1017  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1018  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_engine(get(), &c_engine),
1019  "could not get an engine from a stream object");
1020  return engine(c_engine, true);
1021  }
1022 
1025  stream &wait() {
1026  error::wrap_c_api(
1027  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1028  return *this;
1029  }
1030 };

1816  struct desc {
1817  friend struct memory;
1819  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1820 
1823  desc() : data() {}
1824 
1840  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag,
1841  bool allow_empty = false)
1842  : data() {
1843  validate_dims(adims);
1844  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1845  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
1846  convert_to_c(aformat_tag));
1847  if (!allow_empty)
1848  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1849  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1850  "format tag");
1851  }
1852 
1868  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &strides,
1869  bool allow_empty = false)
1870  : data() {
1871  validate_dims(adims);
1872  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)adims.size());
1873  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1874  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
1875  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1876  if (!allow_empty)
1877  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1878  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1879  "strides");
1880  }
1881 
1885  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1886 
1889  //
1898  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets,
1899  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1900  validate_dims(adims, data.ndims);
1901  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1902  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1903  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1904  &sub_md, &data, adims.data(), offsets.data());
1905  if (!allow_empty)
1906  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1907  return desc(sub_md);
1908  }
1909 
1954  desc reshape(const dims &adims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1955  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(adims, 1);
1956  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1957  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1958  &out_md, &data, (int)adims.size(), adims.data());
1959  if (!allow_empty)
1960  error::wrap_c_api(
1961  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1962  return desc(out_md);
1963  }
1964 
2002  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
2003  bool allow_empty = false) const {
2004  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
2005  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
2006  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
2007  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
2008  if (!allow_empty)
2009  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2010  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
2011  return desc(out_md);
2012  }
2013 
2018  memory::dims dims() const {
2019  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
2020  }
2021 
2024  memory::data_type data_type() const {
2025  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
2026  }
2027 
2032  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
2033 
2037  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
2038 
2043  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
2044  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
2045  }
2046 
2051  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
2052 
2056  explicit operator bool() const { return data.ndims != 0; }
2057  };
2058 
2063  memory() = default;
2064 
2084  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine, void *handle) {

2086  error::wrap_c_api(
2087  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, aengine.get(), handle),
2088  "could not create a memory object");
2089  reset(result);
2090  }
2091 
2098  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine)
2099  : memory(md, aengine, DNNL_MEMORY_ALLOCATE) {}

2458  void get_params_dw_k3s1p1(int index, memory::data_type &weights_data_type,
2459  memory::data_type &bias_data_type, memory::data_type &dst_data_type,
2460  int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
2461 
2462  dnnl_data_type_t c_weights_data_type;
2463  dnnl_data_type_t c_bias_data_type;
2464  dnnl_data_type_t c_dst_data_type;
2465  dnnl_dim_t count;
2466  int c_mask;
2467  const float *c_scales;
2468  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_post_ops_get_params_dw_k3s1p1(get(), index,
2469  &c_weights_data_type, &c_bias_data_type,
2470  &c_dst_data_type, &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
2471  "could not get parameters of depthwise post-op");
2472 
2473  weights_data_type = static_cast<memory::data_type>(c_weights_data_type);
2474  bias_data_type = static_cast<memory::data_type>(c_bias_data_type);
2475  dst_data_type = static_cast<memory::data_type>(c_dst_data_type);
2476  scales.resize(count);
2477 
2478  mask = c_mask;
2479  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
2480  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
2481  return;
2482  }

3102  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
3103  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
3104  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
3105  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
3106  query::exec_arg_md};
3107  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
3108  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
3109  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3110  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
3111 
3112  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
3113  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
3114  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
3115  }

3285  primitive_desc_base(
3286  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3287  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3288 
3300  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3301  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind aprop_kind)
3302  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, aprop_kind, aprop_kind) {}
3303 
3317  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3318  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3319  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3320  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3321  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3322 
3323  dnnl_status_t rc;
3324 
3325  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3326  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3327  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3328 
3329  // Check that primitive kind matches
3330  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3331  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3332  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3333  error::wrap_c_api(
3334  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3335  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3336  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3337  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3338 
3339  // Check that propagation kind matches
3340  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3341  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3342  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3343 
3344  // Something went wrong
3345  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3346  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3347  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3348  "descriptor");
3349 
3350  // Everything is fine
3351  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3352  || (rc == dnnl_success
3353  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3354  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3355  reset_with_clone(pd);
3356  return;
3357  }
3358 
3359  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3360  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3361  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3362  }
3363 
3364  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3365 };

3404  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,

3514 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3515  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {

3690  memory::desc src_desc(int idx = 0) const { return base::src_desc(idx); }
3691 
3693  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
3694  };
3695 
3697  sum() = default;
3698 
3701  sum(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
3702 };
3703 
3705 
3708 
3711 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3712  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3713 
3714  primitive_desc() = default;
3715 
3738  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3739  const engine &aengine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3740  bool allow_empty = false)
3741  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3742  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3743  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3744  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, aengine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3745  if (!allow_empty)
3746  error::wrap_c_api(
3747  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3748  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3749  fetch_impl();
3750  }
3751 
3756  bool next_impl() {
3757  dnnl_status_t status
3758  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3759  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3760  error::wrap_c_api(
3761  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3762  fetch_impl();
3763  return true;
3764  }
3765 
3766 private:
3767  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3768  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3769  void fetch_impl() {
3770  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3771  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3772  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3773  : dnnl_out_of_memory,
3774  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3775  "descriptor iterator");
3776  reset(pd);
3777  }
3778 };

7426  return base::query_md(query::exec_arg_md, DNNL_ARG_DIFF_DST_ITER_C);
7427  }
7428 
7429 protected:
7430  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7431 
7432  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7433  //
7434  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7435  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7436  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7437  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7438  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7439  //
7440  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7441  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7442  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7443  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7444  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7445  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7446  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7447  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7448  dnnl_status_t rc;
7449  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7450  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7451  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7452  "for an RNN primitive");
7453 
7454  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7455  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7456  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7457 
7458  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7459  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7460  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7461  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7462 
7463  if (!ok)
7464  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7465  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7466  "RNN primitive");
7467 
7468  reset_with_clone(pd);
7469  }
7470 };

9796 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
9798  struct desc {
9799  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
9800 
9816  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9817  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9818  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9819  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9820  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), nullptr,
9821  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9822  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9823  }
9824 
9836  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9837  const std::vector<float> &factors,
9838  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
9839  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9840  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9841  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9842  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), &factors[0],
9843  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
9844  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9845  }
9846 
9863  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9864  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
9865  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9866  if (!factors.empty())
9867  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
9868  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9869  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9870  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), factors.data(),
9871  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9872  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9873  }
9874  };

10763 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {
10764  dnnl_primitive_t result;
10765  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_create(&result, c_pd),
10766  "could not create a primitive");
10767  reset(result);
10768 }
10769 
10770 inline primitive::primitive(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
10771 
10772 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &astream,
10773  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10774  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10775  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10776  for (const auto &a : args)
10777  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10778 
10779  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
10780  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10781  "could not execute a primitive");
10782 }
